Nigeria’s D’Tigers will now meet Cote D’Ivoire on Friday at the City Arena in Guangzhou, in their opening match of the classification round at the 2019 FIBA World Cup in China.<img class="size-full wp-image-1247802 aligncenter" src="https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/basket-ball.gif?resize=640%2C640&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="640" height="640" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The match is the first game for the Nigerian male senior team in the classification 17-32 of the competition, and will come up at 1600hrs (0900hrs Nigeria time). They will go on to take on China at the same venue on Sunday. Serena advances to U. S. Open quarter-finals in spite ankle injury(Opens in a new browser tab) Nigeria had finished third from the competition’s Group B on Wednesday, dropping to the classification round which can in the long run give them a ticket to the 2020 Olympic Games.(NAN) Vanguard Nigeria’s D’ Tigers have lost their opening game of the FIBA World Cup. They fell to Russia  82-77 a in Group B match up at the Wuhan Arena. September 1, 2019 In "News" The Federation of International Basketball (FIBA Africa), has announced Lagos, for the second time, as the host of the 2019 FIBA Men’s World Cup qualifiers. July 21, 2018 In "Sports" Nigeria’s men senior basketball team, D’Tigers, capped an impressive run at the just-concluded round of qualifiers for the International Basketball Federation (FIBA) World Cup finishing undefeated. February 26, 2018 In "News"